<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Staying Current with Dictionary Changes</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Follow NASPA/WESPA announcements:</span> Both organisations publish new word lists months before they take effect in tournaments, giving players time to study additions.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Study new additions in batches:</span> When hundreds of words are added at once, prioritise short words (2-5 letters) and those using high-value tiles — they'll impact your game most.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use updated word checkers:</span> Online tools like ScrabbleWordsFinder update their databases when new dictionaries are released. Always verify against the latest edition.</p>
  </div>
</div>

